text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia robiniae is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Great Southern and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 0.7 metres (1 to 2 ft). It blooms from April to September and produces white-cream flowers.
